5300|"          Laugh in their sleeve at tricks they disapprove,"|FALSE
5300|"          And, false or true, a muscle never move."|FALSE
5300|"          A playful jest can scarcely give offence:"|FALSE
5300|"          Who knows too much, oft shows a want of sense."|FALSE
5300|"          From flatt'ry oft more dire effects arise,"|FALSE
5300|"          Enflame the heart and take it by surprise;"|FALSE
5300|"          Ye beauteous belles, beware each sighing swain,"|FALSE
5300|"          Discard his vows:--my book with care retain;"|FALSE
5300|"          Your safety then I'll guarantee at ease.--"|FALSE
5300|"          But why dismiss?--their wishes are to please:"|FALSE
5300|"          And, truly, no necessity appears"|FALSE
5300|"          For solitude:--consider well your years."|FALSE
5300|"          I HAVE, and feel convinced they do you wrong,"|FALSE
5300|"          Who think no virtue can to such belong;"|FALSE
5300|"          White crows and phoenixes do not abound;"|FALSE
5300|"          But lucky lovers still are sometimes found;"|FALSE
5300|"          And though, as these famed birds, not quite so rare,"|FALSE
5300|"          The numbers are not great that favours share;"|FALSE
5300|"          I own my works a diff'rent sense express,"|FALSE
5300|"          But these are tales:--mere tales in easy dress."|FALSE
5300|"          To beauty's wiles, in ev'ry class, I've bowed;"|FALSE
5300|"          Fawned, flattered, sighed, e'en constancy have vowed"|FALSE
5300|"          What gained? you ask--but little I admit;"|FALSE
5300|"          Howe'er we aim, too oft we fail to hit."|FALSE
5300|"          My latter days I'll now devote with care,"|FALSE
5300|"          To guard the sex from ev'ry latent snare."|FALSE
5300|"          Tales I'll detail, and these relate at ease:"|FALSE
5300|"          Narrations clear and neat will always please;"|FALSE
5300|"          Like me, to this attention criticks pay;"|FALSE
5300|"          Then sleep, on either side, from night till day."|FALSE
5300|"          If awkward, vulgar phrase intervene,"|FALSE
5300|"          Or rhymes imperfect o'er the page be seen,"|FALSE
