5300|"          Pass, shut your eyes, who'd heed the idle part?"|FALSE
5300|"          Some mothers, husbands, may perhaps be led,"|FALSE
5300|"          To pull my locks for stories white or red;"|FALSE
5300|"          So matters stand: a fine affair, no doubt,"|FALSE
5300|"          And what I've failed to do--my book makes out."|FALSE
5300|"          THE FAIR my pages safely may pursue,"|FALSE
5300|"          And this apology they'll not refuse."|FALSE
5300|"          What recompense can I presume to make?"|FALSE
5300|"          A tale I'll give, where female charms partake,"|FALSE
5300|"          And prove resistless whatsoe'er assail:"|FALSE
5300|"          Blessed BEAUTY, NATURE ever should prevail."|FALSE
5300|"          HAD Fate decreed our YOUTH, at early morn,"|FALSE
5300|"          To view the angel features you adorn,"|FALSE
5300|"          The captivating pow'rs AURORA bless,"|FALSE
5300|"          Or airy SPRING bedecked in beauteous dress,"|FALSE
5300|"          And all the azure canopy on high"|FALSE
5300|"          Had vanished like a dream, once you were nigh."|FALSE
5300|"          And when his eyes at length your charms beheld,"|FALSE
5300|"          His glowing breast with softest passion swelled;"|FALSE
5300|"          Superior lustre beamed at ev'ry view;"|FALSE
5300|"          No pleasures pleased: his soul was fixed on you."|FALSE
5300|"          Crowns, jewels, palaces, appeared as naught."|FALSE
5300|"          'Twas solely beauteous woman now he sought."|FALSE
5300|"          A WOOD, from earliest years, his home had been,"|FALSE
5300|"          And birds the only company he'd seen,"|FALSE
5300|"          Whose notes harmonious often lulled his care,"|FALSE
5300|"          Beguiled his hours, and saved him from despair;"|FALSE
5300|"          Delightful sounds! from nightingale and dove"|FALSE
5300|"          Unknown their tongue, yet indicant of love."|FALSE
5300|"          THIS savage, solitary, rustick school,"|FALSE
5300|"          The father chose his infancy to rule."|FALSE
5300|"          The mother's recent death induced the sire,"|FALSE
5300|"          To place the son where only beasts retire;"|FALSE
5300|"          And long the forest habitants alone"|FALSE
5300|"          Were all his youthful sight had ever known."|FALSE
5300|"          TWO reasons, good or bad, the father led"|FALSE
5300|"          To fly the world:--all intercourse to dread"|FALSE
5300|"          Since fate had torn his lovely spouse from hence;"|FALSE
5300|"          Misanthropy and fear o'ercame each sense;"|FALSE
5300|"          Of the world grown tired, he hated all around:--"|FALSE
5300|"          Too oft in solitude is sorrow found."|FALSE
5300|"          His partner's death produced distaste of life,"|FALSE
5300|"          And made him fear to seek another wife."|FALSE
5300|"          A hermit's gloomy, mossy cell he took,"|FALSE
5300|"          And wished his child might thither solely look."|FALSE
5300|"          AMONG the poor his little wealth he threw,"|FALSE
5300|"          And with his infant son alone withdrew;"|FALSE
5300|"          The forest's dreary wilds concealed his cell;"|FALSE
5300|"          There Philip (such his name) resolved to dwell."|FALSE
5300|"          BY holy motives led, and not chagrin,"|FALSE
5300|"          The hermit never spoke of what he'd seen;"|FALSE
5300|"          But, from the youth's discernment, strove to hide,"|FALSE
5300|"          Whate'er regarded love, and much beside,"|FALSE
5300|"          The softer sex, with all their magick charms,"|FALSE
5300|"          That fill the feeling bosom with alarms."|FALSE
5300|"          As years advanced, the boy with care he taught;"|FALSE
5300|"          What suited best his age before him brought;"|FALSE
5300|"          At five he showed him animals and flow'rs,"|FALSE
5300|"          The birds of air, the beasts, their sev'ral pow'rs;"|FALSE
5300|"          And now and then of hell he gave a hint,"|FALSE
5300|"          Old Satan's wrath, and what might awe imprint,"|FALSE
5300|"          How formed, and doomed to infamy below;"|FALSE
5300|"          In childhood FEAR 's the lesson first we know!"|FALSE
5300|"          THE years had passed away, when Philip tried,"|FALSE
5300|"          In matters more profound his son to guide;"|FALSE
