5300|"          A sample, now, we have given of his pow'rs,"|FALSE
5300|"          And who would wish for more delightful hours?"|FALSE
5300|"          O grant, kind heav'n! that I the like may meet,"|FALSE
5300|"          And ever prove so wary and discreet."|FALSE
5300|"                    THE MONKS OF CATALONIA"|FALSE
5300|"          TO you, my friends, allow me to detail,"|FALSE
5300|"          The feats of monks in Catalonia's vale,"|FALSE
5300|"          Where oft the holy fathers pow'rs displayed,"|FALSE
5300|"          And showed such charity to wife and maid,"|FALSE
5300|"          That o'er their minds sweet fascination reigned,"|FALSE
5300|"          And made them think, they Paradise had gained."|FALSE
5300|"          SUCH characters oft preciously advise,"|FALSE
5300|"          And youthful easy female minds surprise,"|FALSE
5300|"          The beauteous FAIR encircle with their net,"|FALSE
5300|"          And, of the feeling heart, possession get:"|FALSE
5300|"          Work in the holy vineyard, you may guess,"|FALSE
5300|"          And, as our tale will show, with full success."|FALSE
5300|"          IN times of old, when learning 'mong the FAIR,"|FALSE
5300|"          Enough to read the testament, was rare,"|FALSE
