5300|"                     THE RIVER SCAMANDER"|FALSE
5300|"          I'M now disposed to give a pretty tale;"|FALSE
5300|"          Love laughs at what I've sworn and will prevail;"|FALSE
5300|"          Men, gods, and all, his mighty influence know,"|FALSE
5300|"          And full obedience to the urchin show."|FALSE
5300|"          In future when I celebrate his flame,"|FALSE
5300|"          Expressions not so warm will be my aim;"|FALSE
5300|"          I would not willingly abuses plant,"|FALSE
5300|"          But rather let my writings spirit want."|FALSE
5300|"          If in these verses I around should twirl,"|FALSE
5300|"          Some wily knave and easy simple girl,"|FALSE
5300|"          'Tis with intention in the breast to place;"|FALSE
5300|"          On such occasions, dread of dire disgrace;"|FALSE
5300|"          The mind to open, and the sex to set"|FALSE
5300|"          Upon their guard 'gainst snares so often met."|FALSE
5300|"          Gross ignorance a thousand has misled,"|FALSE
5300|"          For one that has been hurt by what I've said."|FALSE
5300|"          I'VE read that once, an orator renowned"|FALSE
5300|"          In Greece, where arts superior then were found,"|FALSE
