5300|"          Of all devouring Time the prey and sport."|FALSE
5300|"          O TROY! for me thy very name has got"|FALSE
5300|"          Superior charms:--in story fruitful spot;"|FALSE
5300|"          Thy famed remains I ne'er can hope to view,"|FALSE
5300|"          That gods by labour raised, and gods o'erthrew;"|FALSE
5300|"          Those fields where daring acts of valour shone;"|FALSE
5300|"          So many fights were lost:--so many won."|FALSE
5300|"          BUT to resume my thread, and not extend"|FALSE
5300|"          Too much the subjects which our plan suspend;"|FALSE
5300|"          This Cymon, who's the hero of our tale,"|FALSE
5300|"          When walking near the banks that form the dale"|FALSE
5300|"          Through which Scamander's waters freely flow,"|FALSE
5300|"          Observed a youthful charmer thither go,"|FALSE
5300|"          To breathe the cool refreshing breeze around;"|FALSE
5300|"          That on its verdant borders oft she'd found."|FALSE
5300|"          Her veil was floating, and her artless dress,"|FALSE
5300|"          A shepherdess seemed clearly to express."|FALSE
5300|"          Tall, elegantly formed, with beauteous mien,"|FALSE
5300|"          And ev'ry feature lovely to be seen,"|FALSE
5300|"          Young Cymon felt emotion and surprise,"|FALSE
5300|"          And thought 'twas Venus that had caught his eyes,"|FALSE
5300|"          Who on the river's side her charms displayed,"|FALSE
5300|"          Those wondrous treasures all perfection made."|FALSE
5300|"          A GROT was nigh, to which the simple fair,"|FALSE
5300|"          Not dreaming ills, was anxious to repair;"|FALSE
5300|"          The heat, some evil spirit, and the place,"|FALSE
5300|"          Invited her the moment to embrace,"|FALSE
5300|"          To bathe within the stream that near her ran;"|FALSE
5300|"          And instantly her project she began."|FALSE
5300|"          THE spark concealed himself; each charm admired;"|FALSE
5300|"          Now this, now that, now t'other feature fired;"|FALSE
5300|"          A hundred beauties caught his eager sight;"|FALSE
5300|"          And while his bosom felt supreme delight,"|FALSE
5300|"          He turned his thoughts advantages to take,"|FALSE
5300|"          And of the maiden's error something make;"|FALSE
5300|"          Assumed the character, and dress; and air;"|FALSE
5300|"          That should a wat'ry deity declare;"|FALSE
5300|"          Within the gliding flood his vestments dipt:"|FALSE
5300|"          A crown of rushes on his head he slipt;"|FALSE
5300|"          Aquatick herbs and plants around he twined:"|FALSE
5300|"          Then Mercury intreated to be kind,"|FALSE
5300|"          And Cupid too, the wily god of hearts;"|FALSE
5300|"          How could the innocent resist these arts?"|FALSE
5300|"          AT length a foot so fair the belle exposed,"|FALSE
5300|"          E'en Galatea never such disclosed;"|FALSE
5300|"          The stream, that glided by, received the prize;"|FALSE
5300|"          Her lilies she beheld with downcast eyes,"|FALSE
5300|"          And, half ashamed, herself surveyed at ease,"|FALSE
5300|"          While round the zephyrs wantoned in the breeze."|FALSE
5300|"          WHEN thus engaged, the lover near her drew;"|FALSE
5300|"          At whose approach away the damsel flew,"|FALSE
5300|"          And tried to hide within the rocky cell;"|FALSE
5300|"          Cried Cymon, I beneath these waters dwell,"|FALSE
5300|"          And o'er their course a sov'reign right maintain;"|FALSE
