5300|"          If worthy of yourself the flood you deem;"|FALSE
5300|"          Too happy should this honour you bestow,"|FALSE
5300|"          And with me, 'neath the current, freely go."|FALSE
5300|"          Your fair companions, ev'ry one I'll make"|FALSE
5300|"          A nymph of fountains, hill, or grove, or lake;"|FALSE
5300|"          My pow'r is great, extending far around"|FALSE
5300|"          Where'er the eye can reach, 'tis fully found."|FALSE
5300|"          THE eloquence he used, her fears and dread;"|FALSE
5300|"          Lest she might give offence by what she said,"|FALSE
5300|"          In spite of bashfulness that bliss alloys,"|FALSE
5300|"          Soon all concluded with celestial joys."|FALSE
5300|"          'Tis even said that Cupid lent supplies;"|FALSE
5300|"          From superstition many things arise."|FALSE
