5300|"                A CONFIDANT WITHOUT KNOWING IT;"|FALSE
5300|"                             OR"|FALSE
5300|"                       THE STRATAGEM"|FALSE
5300|"          NO master sage, nor orator I know,"|FALSE
5300|"          Who can success, like gentle Cupid show;"|FALSE
5300|"          His ways and arguments are pleasing smiles,"|FALSE
5300|"          Engaging looks, soft tears, and winning wiles."|FALSE
5300|"          Wars in his empire will at times arise,"|FALSE
5300|"          And, in the field, his standard meet the eyes;"|FALSE
5300|"          Now stealing secretly, with skilful lure."|FALSE
5300|"          He penetrates to hearts supposed secure,"|FALSE
5300|"          O'erleaps the ramparts that protect around,"|FALSE
5300|"          And citadels reduces, most renowned."|FALSE
5300|"          I DARE engage, two fortresses besiege"|FALSE
5300|"          Leave one to Mars, and t'other to this liege."|FALSE
5300|"          And though the god of war should numbers bring,"|FALSE
5300|"          With all the arms that can his thunders fling,"|FALSE
5300|"          Before the fort he'll vainly waste his time,"|FALSE
5300|"          While Cupid, unattended, in shall climb,"|FALSE
5300|"          Obtain possession perfectly at ease,"|FALSE
5300|"          And grant conditions just as he shall please."|FALSE
5300|"          I NOW propose to give a fav'rite tale:--"|FALSE
5300|"          The god of Love was never known to fail,"|FALSE
5300|"          In finding stratagems, as I have read,"|FALSE
5300|"          And many have I seen most nicely spread."|FALSE
5300|"          THE young Aminta was Gerontes' wife,"|FALSE
5300|"          With whom she lived, it seems, a wretched life."|FALSE
5300|"          Far better she deserved than what she had,"|FALSE
5300|"          For he was jealous, and his temper bad:"|FALSE
5300|"          An aged hunks, while she was in the hour"|FALSE
5300|"          When hearts, that never felt LOVE'S mighty pow'r,"|FALSE
5300|"          Are presently by tender objects caught,"|FALSE
5300|"          Which ne'er before had entered in the thought."|FALSE
5300|"          WHEN first Aminta saw young Cleon's face,"|FALSE
5300|"          A lad possessing all engaging grace,"|FALSE
5300|"          Much prudence then she ev'ry way displayed,"|FALSE
5300|"          E'en more perhaps than necessary made."|FALSE
5300|"          For though we may suppose the lovely fair,"|FALSE
5300|"          Would ev'ry effort use to 'scape the snare,"|FALSE
5300|"          Yet when the god of soft persuasion takes"|FALSE
5300|"          The fatal moment, havock soon he makes,"|FALSE
5300|"          In vain his duty, any thing opposed,"|FALSE
5300|"          If once the tender sentiment's disclosed."|FALSE
5300|"          Aminta consolation had in view"|FALSE
5300|"          'Twas that alone the passion from her drew,"|FALSE
5300|"          A meeting innocent, to vent her tears,"|FALSE
5300|"          And, to a feeling friend, express her fears."|FALSE
5300|"          'Tis represented thus I cannot doubt;"|FALSE
5300|"          But sight of meat brings appetite about;"|FALSE
5300|"          And if you would avoid the tempting bit,"|FALSE
5300|"          'Tis better far at table not to sit."|FALSE
5300|"          AMINTA hoped to render Cleon kind;"|FALSE
5300|"          Poor innocent! as yet to dangers blind,"|FALSE
5300|"          These conversations she was led to deem,"|FALSE
5300|"          Mere friendly ways that raised sincere esteem;"|FALSE
5300|"          And this alone she ardently desired,"|FALSE
5300|"          Without supposing more would be required,"|FALSE
5300|"          Or any thing improper be the case:"|FALSE
5300|"          She'd rather die than suffer such disgrace."|FALSE
5300|"          'Twas difficult the business to commence;"|FALSE
5300|"          A letter 's often lost, or gives offence,"|FALSE
5300|"          And many serious accidents arrive:"|FALSE
5300|"          To have a confidant 'twere better strive;"|FALSE
5300|"          But where could such a female friend be found?"|FALSE
5300|"          Gerontes dreaded was by all around."|FALSE
5300|"          I've said already, Cupid will obtain,"|FALSE
5300|"          One way or t'other, what he wants to gain;"|FALSE
5300|"          And this will show the observation just"|FALSE
5300|"          The maxim's such as you may always trust."|FALSE
5300|"          A FEMALE relative young Cleon had,"|FALSE
5300|"          A peevish prude, who looked upon the lad,"|FALSE
5300|"          As one she had a right to rule and scold;"|FALSE
5300|"          Her name was Mistress Alice: sour and old."|FALSE
5300|"          ONE summer's day, Aminta to her said:"|FALSE
5300|"          I cannot think how 'tis, your cousin's led,"|FALSE
5300|"          (Though quite indifferent he is to me,"|FALSE
5300|"          And doubtless such will ever prove to be)"|FALSE
5300|"          With various fond attentions, to pretend,"|FALSE
5300|"          He loves me--much beyond a common friend."|FALSE
5300|"          My window oft he passes day and night;"|FALSE
5300|"          I cannot move a step, but he's in sight,"|FALSE
5300|"          And in a moment at my heels appears;"|FALSE
5300|"          Notes, letters full of soft expressions, dears,"|FALSE
5300|"          To me are sent by one I will not name,"|FALSE
5300|"          For known to you, she would be thought to blame:"|FALSE
